          Does anyone know who this man is? For everyone who likes Bush and doesn't exactly know why... look up this guy's party affiliation and what he <em>owns</em>.<br /><br /><strong>On another note...</strong> I just wanted to express my feelings a bit about who I am and who we are. I am, we are, Americans. I was, you are, getting fooled into thinking we have small government. I am becoming, you need to be, a political activist until November because there are a lot of weird things going on in the country and as an informed citizen I will do everything I can to show people that things are screwy on the Hill. Robert Murdock owns 3/4 of the world's media sources and he's an extreme Right-Wing politician. 3/4 of the <i>WORLD'S</i> media sources.<br /><br />Screw parties and sides.<br /><br />What is your straight up stance on these issues? Wouldn't you like to know...<blockquote>- truth in the media<br />- the truth about who we're fighting<br />- just how much the church is involved in the government right now<br />- how the economy is doing (screw the Fox filter)...how it's doing in [reality].<br />- where (or who) the tax breaks went to<br />- how many students won't be able to afford school<br />- how many students <b><i>WILL</i></b> resort to getting their education funds from joining the military.</blockquote>Just how many of us gets our opinions from the nightly news? I'm not trying to look cooky here people. Just open your eyes a bit. So John Kerry represents the 'big government' party? You're kidding right? Just rub the sleep out of your view and see how big our government is <strong>right</strong> <strong><u>now</u></strong>.<br />
